havanas shipyard named el arsenal was extremely active thanks to the lumber resources available in the vicinity of the city the  santísima trinidad  was the largest warship of her time  launched in 1769 she was about 62 meters long had three decks and 120 cannons she was later upgraded to as many as 144 cannons and four decks she sank following the  battle of trafalgar  in 1805 this ship cost 40000 pesos fuertes of the time which gives an idea of the importance of the arsenal by comparing its cost to the 26 million pesos fuertes and 109 ships produced during the arsenals existence
